com.sterlingcommerce.ui.web.platform.security

Class SCUIResourcePermission

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.sterlingcommerce.ui.web.platform.security.SCUIResourcePermission
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ISCUIResourcePermission

    public class SCUIResourcePermission
extends java.lang.Object
implements ISCUIResourcePermission
    SCUIResourcePermission defines the permission for a resource given by a ResourceId during the authorization. It represents data from YFS_RESOURCE_PERMISSION table. If a resource's permission is not permission controlled then all the users will have access to the resource given by the resourceId. If a resource's permission is inactive then all the users are denied access to the resource given by the resourceId. If a resource's permission is set as read only then the execute and write permission are denied. rasrinivasan
